news.title: Navi Mumbai police file case against four for cheating interior designer in land deal
news.para: The accused persons sold a piece of land at Pali in Raigad district to the 46-year-old victim for Rs 68.10 lakh, but failed to deliver possession of the property

news.title: Gross leasing of office space to cross 80 million sq ft across eight cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The gross leasing of office space rose 66 per cent to 24.8 million square feet across the top eight cities in Q3 2024, marking the second highest quarterly leasing volume in the sector's history.

news.title: Bhaane Retail buys South Mumbai’s Rhythm House through insolvency auction
news.para: In February 2020, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) ordered the liquidation of Rhythm House, which had been seized by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) in 2018 during its investigation into the Punjab National Bank scam involving Modi.

news.title: Delhi LG approves land acquisition for Aerocity-Tughlakabad metro corridor
news.para: Delhi Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena has approved the acquisition of land measuring 1,688 square metre at Khanpur Village in south Delhi, they said.

news.title: Mysore development body set to resume site auctions
news.para: Muda, having acquired 14 sites relinquished by chief minister Siddaramaiah's wife, Parvathi, will also auction these sites, but only after the culmination of the ongoing inquiry into the alleged scam.

news.title: Sebi to auction 15 properties of five companies on November 19
news.para: The move is part of Sebi's efforts to recover money collected by these companies from investors in violation of norms. Properties that will go under the hammer including flats, land with structure and land parcels are located in West Bengal and Odisha.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to blacklist Sanghani Infrastructure for delays in Thaltej housing project
news.para: The civic body has now decided to blacklist Sanghani Infrastructure India Pvt Ltd for five years, a proposal for which was presented at the housing committee meeting on Oct 16.

news.title: Maharashtra: Property registrations to be disrupted from October 18-21 due to system upgrade
news.para: Up to 13,000 properties are registered in the state every day. "The upgrade in the Government Receipt Accounting System (GRAS) was to be carried out last week, but postponed owing to Dasara festivities.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body refunds excess charges to developers in Bopal TP schemes
news.para: ​​These charges were levied in cases where Auda could not deduct the entire 40% land as mandated under the Town Planning Act. The lesser deductions had happened since development had already taken place on some under the Bopal TP schemes 1,2 and 3.

news.title: Godrej Properties wins bid to develop 6.5 acres plots in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The plots, measuring 6.54 acres, will offer a development potential of about two million sq ft, comprising residential apartments of varied configurations, with an estimated combined revenue potential of about Rs 3,500 crore.

news.title: Kerala HC quashes writ petition by Dragonstone Realty
news.para: The court stated it could not intervene in the case where National Green Tribunal (NGT) is the appellate authority. Dragonstone Realty is the special purpose vehicle (SPV) formed to develop the non-SEZ part of the Taurus Downtown Trivandrum project.

news.title: Chennai: Majority of Jains Westminster apartments owners agree for redevelopment
news.para: While reconstruction means rebuilding a structure exactly as it is, redevelopment implies construction of a new structure with a completely new plan and dimension.

news.title: Karnataka HC upholds BDA's right to reject auction bids without explanation
news.para: A division bench consisting of Justice Anu Sivaraman and Justice G Basavaraja concluded that the BDA's decision was lawful, aligning with the public interest and benefiting the general public.

news.title: NCDRC orders Godrej Projects to refund Rs 4 crore to homebuyers
news.para: Godrej Projects to refund over Rs 4 crore to homebuyers in five separate cases for its failure to deliver its promises, which included a 24-metre-wide road and other essential amenities even seven years after making bookings. The homebuyers had booked flats in the ‘Godrej Summit' project in Sector 104 in Gurgaon.

news.title: Homebuyers in Karnataka urges completion of housing act amendments
news.para: This announcement delighted lakhs of homebuyers, but eight months later, the government is yet to come out with the draft of the proposed Karnataka Apartment Ownership Act.

news.title: KBC Global plans to raise Rs 100 crore through issue of equity shares
news.para: The board of the company will meet on October 16 (Wednesday) to consider and approve a proposal to raise up to Rs 100 crore through an issue of equity shares via permissible modes, including preferential allotment and warrants, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Maharashtra government clears Deonar dumping ground for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: The state cabinet on Monday approved handing over 124 acres of Deonar dumping ground, the city's oldest and largest landfill spanning 311 acres, for the project.

news.title: Pune: MPCB issues show-cause notice to IT firm for noise and dust at under construction site
news.para: In the notice, MPCB stated that the firm had exceeded the noise limits during the construction of its new tower in Kalyaninagar. Besides, the pollution board also found water being discharged into the nearby nullah during the excavation work of the building.

news.title: Private equity investment in real estate down 4% to $2.3 billion in H1 FY25: Anarock
news.para: ​​ Real estate consultant Anarock noted that the total number of deals declined to 17 in April-September this year from 24 in the corresponding period of the preceding year.

news.title: Garuda Construction shares surge over 10% in market debut on October 15
news.para: The stock listed at Rs 103.20, a jump of 8.63 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. Later, it surged 15.55 per cent to Rs 109.78.
